                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The final text of the proposed peace treaty, with two declarations by the
                    Government of Japan and a protocol, dated August 13, was released simultaneously
                    by its joint sponsors, the United Kingdom and the United States, at 4:00 p. m.
                    August 15. For text, with revisions to the July 20 text, see Department of State
                        <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, August 27, 1951, page 349.</p>
                <p>For revisions to the July 3 draft as of July 20, see circular telegram 57, July
                    18, <ref target="#pg_1199">page 1199</ref>.</p>
                <p>For revisions to the draft of June 14 as of July 3, see circular telegram 9, July
                    3, <ref target="#pg_1174">page 1174</ref>.</p>
                <p>For the draft of June 14, see <ref target="#pg_1119">page 1119</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
